## What this presentation must NOT do

1. Ask for a specific budget (that comes later with Diego)
2. Share P&L, revenue, EBITDA, or gross margin data
3. Present a status update or project reporting
4. Mention restructuring or layoffs (speak of "capability evolution")
5. Overclaim capabilities we don't have (use NOW/Q2/Q3/Q4+ velocity markers)
6. Treat regulation as background context (it's a business line with $492M market)
7. Organize the offer by technology capability (organize by sales logic: entry → expansion → recurring)
8. Present Alkemy+ as "the same thing with AI" (it must be genuinely innovative)
9. Separate data from tech in DTC (they go unified)
10. Place GEO outside Media, or UX/UI outside Data.Tech.AI
11. Present Helvetia as a BX project (it's cross-practice)
12. Present a fixed catalog (what we sell is quarterly adaptation)

